It's not as simple as whether I
did or did not try to kill the Pope.

188
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,798
How could it possibly
not be that simple?

189
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:31,769
Dr. Kapoor coated the bed in the
presidential bay with a known poison.

190
00:09:32,205 --> 00:09:34,538
Sorry. Poison? It
was oleander petals!

191
00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:36,439
Which are poisonous.
But it was a gift.

192
00:09:36,509 --> 00:09:38,978
It represents heart chakra.
Pope has a big heart.

193
00:09:39,145 --> 00:09:42,047
Yeah, Vijay, couldn't you just
have given the Pope a normal gift?

194
00:09:42,615 --> 00:09:46,279
I would have, but what do you give
someone who lives in the Vatican?

195
00:09:46,453 --> 00:09:47,819
Pope is a man of peace.

196
00:09:48,221 --> 00:09:50,713
He supports women's
rights and gay people.

197
00:09:51,124 --> 00:09:53,889
In fact, I heard a rumor that
he sneaks out of the Vatican,

198
00:09:53,993 --> 00:09:56,656
disguised, to help to
feed the poor people.

199
00:09:57,330 --> 00:10:00,698
As you can see, Dr. Kapoor
made an innocent mistake.

200
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:01,824
He loves the Pope.

201
00:10:02,035 --> 00:10:04,197
I love the Pope. Loves him.

202
00:10:09,476 --> 00:10:11,069
Your background
check came back clear.

203
00:10:11,177 --> 00:10:13,476
So he can go, right?

204
00:10:16,182 --> 00:10:18,151
I'll check. Great. Thank you.

205
00:10:18,885 --> 00:10:20,685
I mean, if I actually
wanted to kill the Pope,

206
00:10:20,753 --> 00:10:22,984
I would have used
white snakeroot petals.

207
00:10:23,423 --> 00:10:26,257
Excuse me? Yeah, it's
faster and untraceable.

208
00:10:26,359 --> 00:10:29,557
That's exactly what killed
Abraham Lincoln's mother, you know.

209
00:10:30,396 --> 00:10:31,887
Take a seat, please, Dr. Kapoor.

210
00:10:32,398 --> 00:10:34,663
What? You're on your own, pal.

211
00:10:35,902 --> 00:10:37,165
Please take a seat.

212
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:47,105
So, Jimmy's heart biopsy results

213
00:10:47,347 --> 00:10:50,283
