and that should
treat this episode,

217
00:10:56,122 --> 00:10:58,682
but we need to find out why
it happened in the first place.

218
00:10:58,758 --> 00:11:03,093
Now, were there any changes in his
diet? Any rashes, colds or upset stomach?

219
00:11:04,697 --> 00:11:05,892
Hmm.

220
00:11:06,232 --> 00:11:09,634
Well, can you think of anything different?
Like, anything out of the ordinary?

221
00:11:17,443 --> 00:11:18,467
Mrs. Corrigan?

222
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:23,606
Our insurance paid
for the transplant,

223
00:11:23,883 --> 00:11:26,785
but they didn't pay for any
of the post-op medications.

224
00:11:27,954 --> 00:11:29,252
Doesn't make any sense.

225
00:11:30,256 --> 00:11:33,226
The pills, they cost
over $9,000 a month.

226
00:11:36,095 --> 00:11:38,724
Our church held a fundraiser,
but it wasn't enough.

227
00:11:39,832 --> 00:11:41,164
Okay. And?

228
00:11:42,936 --> 00:11:46,304
We started
spreading out the pills.

229
00:11:47,607 --> 00:11:51,237
Like, just giving him
one every other day.

230
00:11:51,945 --> 00:11:53,470
We were trying
to make them last.

231
00:11:55,915 --> 00:11:57,008
Um...

232
00:11:57,517 --> 00:11:58,917
That's what made Jimmy sick.

233
00:11:59,986 --> 00:12:01,113
We did this.

234
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:04,851
Well, I mean... It's real
easy to blame yourselves.

235
00:12:05,358 --> 00:12:07,293
That's not gonna make
Jimmy better, okay?

236
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:09,480
We just need to make sure
that it never happens again.

237
00:12:09,662 --> 00:12:11,756
All right? But it will.

238
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:14,131
We can't afford the pills.

239
00:12:15,702 --> 00:12:17,295
What are we supposed to do?

240
00:12:23,376 --> 00:12:25,038
I'm just doing my job.

241
00:12:25,144 --> 00:12:26,806
Walter's living will
specifically states

242
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:29,178
any and all known medical
treatments should be explored.

243
00:12:29,515 --> 00:12:31,780
Okay. But Sheila?

