residence and ran away with him.

246
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:38,449
They're in love.

247
00:12:38,725 --> 00:12:42,389
Look, I'm just trying to protect
Walter from the story I see all the time.

248
00:12:42,862 --> 00:12:45,457
An older man, alone, vulnerable,
meets a younger woman...

249
00:12:45,865 --> 00:12:46,992
She's 75.

250
00:12:47,066 --> 00:12:50,468
Twenty-five or 75, she wants
him to stop his cancer treatment.

251
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:53,382
Now, I've been granted his
healthcare decisions because frankly,

252
00:12:53,406 --> 00:12:55,204
his healthcare proxy
was asleep at the wheel.

253
00:12:55,642 --> 00:12:58,669
So here I am,
doing the best I can.

254
00:13:01,547 --> 00:13:02,810
I can appreciate that.

255
00:13:03,316 --> 00:13:04,750
So, tell me.

256
00:13:05,818 --> 00:13:08,014
Is stopping treatment in
Walter's best interests?

257
00:13:08,154 --> 00:13:09,486
Medically, no.

258
00:13:10,323 --> 00:13:12,019
But I have to respect
the patient's wishes.

259
00:13:12,525 --> 00:13:15,017
Well, legally, you have
to respect my wishes.

260
00:13:15,695 --> 00:13:19,894
And even though Walt's a pain in
the ass, I'm just trying to keep him alive.

261
00:13:21,768 --> 00:13:23,008
<i>He's trying to kill me.</i>

262
00:13:23,436 --> 00:13:29,103
If it were left up to Carl, I would
be alone, rotting in my apartment,

263
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:31,677
having the life
drained out of me.

264
00:13:33,079 --> 00:13:34,672
He's doing what
he thinks is best.

265
00:13:35,348 --> 00:13:37,715
He thinks Sheila pushed me.

266
00:13:37,950 --> 00:13:39,384
The whole thing was my idea.

267
00:13:40,086 --> 00:13:42,681
Unfortunately, the law
may not see it that way.

268
00:13:42,789 --> 00:13:46,055
I don't have a lot of
time left on this Earth.

269
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:49,954
And the law won't let
me live the way I want to.

270
00:13:51,564 --> 00:13:52,691
That ain't right.

271
00:13:59,706 --> 00:14:01,868
Maybe there is
something that we can do.

272
00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:04,467
Get the law on our side.

273
00:14:06,913 --> 00:14:08,142
Max. How can I help?

274
00:14:08,548 --> 00:14:11,279
Change the fundamental
idiocracy of American healthcare?

275
00:14:11,384 --> 00:14:12,408
I'm working on it.

276
00:14:12,485 --> 00:14:14,954
I've got this kid, just
had a heart transplant,

277
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:16,545
family can't afford
the post-op meds.

278
00:14:16,622 --> 00:14:18,056
What's their financial profile?

279
00:14:18,124 --> 00:14:19,490
Married, stable.

280
00:14:19,592 --> 00:14:22,118
Dad's a security guard who
pulls in about 45K a year.

281
00:14:22,228 --> 00:14:23,719
Too much to
qualify for Medicaid.

282
00:14:23,796 --> 00:14:25,059
Or the Community Care Fund.

283
00:14:25,131 --> 00:14:28,898
Well, we can help them in the short
term but they need a long-term solution.

284
00:14:29,135 --> 00:14:31,627
Working class, just
caught in the middle.

285
00:14:34,173 --> 00:14:35,232
Maybe not.

286
00:14:39,445 --> 00:14:40,674
Um...

287
00:14:42,148 --> 00:14:43,446
You could get a divorce.

288
00:14:45,318 --> 00:14:47,287
Is this a joke?

289
00:14:47,754 --> 00:14:50,815
Look, if Patricia is a
single mom with no income,

290
00:14:51,324 --> 00:14:53,088
she and Jimmy could
qualify for Medicaid.

291
00:14:53,292 --> 00:14:55,659
And Medicaid would cover
the cost of Jimmy's medication.

292
00:14:55,762 --> 00:14:57,788
But we love each other.

293
00:14:59,132 --> 00:15:01,033
Well, no one's questioning that.

294
00:15:01,134 --> 00:15:04,036
And as Catholics, we don't
even believe in divorce.

295
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:05,533
You can't ask us to break

296
00:15:05,638 --> 00:15:08,107
something that's
unbreakable. I can't even...

297
00:15:08,174 --> 00:15:12,270
I'm sorry. It's just
this system is flawed.

298
00:15:13,346 --> 00:15:16,510
And so is this solution, but
I can't think of a better one.

299
00:15:20,386 --> 00:15:22,651
Get divorced, save your son.

300
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:31,725
What happened?

301
00:15:31,831 --> 00:15:33,163
I don't know. I
just got the page.

302
00:15:33,499 --> 00:15:35,661
Heart rate 140. BP 90 over
palp. Respiratory rate 22.

303
00:15:35,868 --> 00:15:37,734
She collapsed at work.
EMS just dropped off.

304
00:15:38,237 --> 00:15:40,206
Any history of
infection? No, none.

305
00:15:40,306 --> 00:15:42,639
She's tachy, hypotensive,
warm to the touch.

306
00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:43,732
Sepsis?

307
00:15:43,843 --> 00:15:45,903
She has a hot, red, macular
rash around her J-tube.

308
00:15:46,012 --> 00:15:47,571
Cellulitis. Looks like it.

309
00:15:47,747 --> 00:15:48,806
That's preventable.

310
00:15:48,881 --> 00:15:51,193
Helen, your people let her walk
out with an infection? Who's next?

311
00:15:51,217 --> 00:15:53,379
Max, I paged you here as
her friend, not as her doctor.

312
00:15:53,686 --> 00:15:54,984
Let's get her to Trauma One!

313
00:15:55,321 --> 00:15:56,755
I've got this under control.

314
00:15:56,856 --> 00:15:57,880
Do you?

315
00:16:00,193 --> 00:16:02,685
I'm gonna give you a minute to
think about what you just said.

316
00:16:13,406 --> 00:16:15,932
Max. Birthing class?
Hmm. I'll be there.

317
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:17,501
Okay.

318
00:16:20,780 --> 00:16:22,112
How is she?

319
00:16:22,215 --> 00:16:23,877
She's stable, but
not out of the woods.

320
00:16:23,950 --> 00:16:25,928
Yeah. She was coughing this
morning but there was no indication...

