00:17:52,838 --> 00:17:54,278
That's a joke, right?
You're kidding?

353
00:17:54,507 --> 00:17:56,339
I'm not known for
my sense of humor.

354
00:18:05,051 --> 00:18:06,383
Do you know my password?

355
00:18:09,155 --> 00:18:10,885
The ICU is a secured area, sir.

356
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:12,822
Sure it is, and you're
doing a hell of a job,

357
00:18:12,892 --> 00:18:15,384
but I'm late for a birthing
class and this way's faster,

358
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:18,555
so I'm just gonna go
ahead and... Okay.

359
00:18:19,865 --> 00:18:22,528
That's my ICU, right?
And I'm really late

360
00:18:22,635 --> 00:18:25,799
so I'm just gonna go ahead
and walk through it right now.

361
00:18:25,871 --> 00:18:28,739
So you can just step aside.

362
00:18:30,042 --> 00:18:32,170
Go ahead and just step...

363
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:36,809
Yeah. Did I mention
I have cancer?

364
00:18:47,727 --> 00:18:50,697
<i>When you find out
that you have cancer,</i>

365
00:18:52,198 --> 00:18:53,928
it's the worst moment.

366
00:18:55,101 --> 00:18:57,502
Everything is chaos and...

367
00:18:58,404 --> 00:18:59,667
And fear.

368
00:19:02,008 --> 00:19:03,340
When adult protection services

369
00:19:04,043 --> 00:19:06,706
petitioned to have Mr. Brandt
become a ward of the state,

370
00:19:07,113 --> 00:19:09,446
he had just got his
cancer diagnosis.

371
00:19:10,016 --> 00:19:11,575
He was unraveling.

372
00:19:13,519 --> 00:19:15,010
But then Walter met Sheila.

373
00:19:16,922 --> 00:19:21,792
And since he's been with Sheila,
he's happy and taken care of.

374
00:19:23,763 --> 00:19:26,756
Will love cure Walter? No.

375
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:31,029
But it will heal
him in other ways.

376
00:19:33,072 --> 00:19:34,802
Mr. Jimenez, do
you have a response?

377
00:19:35,274 --> 00:19:36,708
I do, Your Honor.

378
00:19:37,710 --> 00:19:41,078
The decision to deem
Mr. Brandt an incapacitated person

379
00:19:41,147 --> 00:19:42,240
was not made lightly.

380
00:19:42,748 --> 00:19:43,943
Now... Oh, come on.

381
00:19:44,050 --> 00:19:45,916
Mr. Brandt, this
is for your benefit.

382
00:19:46,252 --> 00:19:48,084
You're petitioning to
get your rights back.

383
00:19:48,154 --> 00:19:49,645
Please let Mr. Jimenez finish.

384
00:19:50,589 --> 00:19:51,716
I'm sorry.

385
00:19:51,791 --> 00:19:53,201
Look, I didn't want to go there,

386
00:19:53,225 --> 00:19:56,059
but of the five speeding
tickets Walter got last year,

387
00:19:56,295 --> 00:19:57,495
one of them was near a school.

388
00:19:58,164 --> 00:20:00,827
His hoarding caused a
small fire in his apartment.

389
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:03,493
And then Walter got aggressive
with his healthcare attendant

390
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:05,127
when she tried to
help him clean up.

391
00:20:05,638 --> 00:20:07,573
That's why the state stepped in.

392
00:20:08,274 --> 00:20:10,971
You believe he's a danger
to himself and to others?

393
00:20:15,014 --> 00:20:16,346
I do, Your Honor.

394
00:20:32,498 --> 00:20:33,522
Hey, there.

395
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,798
Can we talk for a minute?

396
00:20:39,972 --> 00:20:44,205
I just wanted to check in. I
know we hit you with a crazy idea.

397
00:20:44,844 --> 00:20:46,844
We were just trying to help
you duck some red tape.

398
00:20:47,113 --> 00:20:49,173
Our marriage isn't red tape.

399
00:20:49,815 --> 00:20:51,044
I realize that.

400
00:20:51,150 --> 00:20:53,779
When Neil and I got
married, we made a promise

401
00:20:54,653 --> 00:20:58,681
to our friends,
our family, to God.

402
00:20:59,058 --> 00:21:02,961
It was a divine pact to each
other. That's a... It's a real promise.

403
00:21:03,028 --> 00:21:04,724
Marriage is forever.

404
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:07,026
I can't even imagine.

405
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,661
Neil is our rock.

406
00:21:08,734 --> 00:21:09,793
Look, Mrs. Corrigan...

407
00:21:09,869 --> 00:21:11,667
I won't abandon my family.

408
00:21:11,737 --> 00:21:15,640
It'd just be on paper. "Render
unto Caesar," that sort of thing.

409
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:16,903
There has to be another way.

410
00:21:17,009 --> 00:21:18,671
We'd lose our community.

411
00:21:19,011 --> 00:21:20,771
We wouldn't be able
to receive the Eucharist.

412
00:21:20,846 --> 00:21:22,212
I understand,

413
00:21:22,481 --> 00:21:24,643
but is that worth more
than your son's life?

414
00:21:30,589 --> 00:21:32,524
Hey, maybe we
could get remarried.

415
00:21:33,192 --> 00:21:35,252
You know, when Jimmy's
off his medications.

416
00:21:38,764 --> 00:21:42,030
Unfortunately, Jimmy will be
on meds for the rest of his life.

417
00:21:46,105 --> 00:21:47,437
This is forever?

418
00:21:48,507 --> 00:21:50,066
I don't see any
other way around it.

419
00:22:01,086 --> 00:22:02,247
Then we'll do it.

420
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:17,099
Inhale.

421
00:22:18,370 --> 00:22:21,431
And exhale.

422
00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:28,036
Okay, moms. Put all your
weight on your partner.

423
00:22:29,415 --> 00:22:31,145
Inhale.

424
00:22:34,119 --> 00:22:36,384
And sway.

425
00:22:37,623 --> 00:22:40,058
Good. Doesn't that feel good?

426
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,058
Are you okay? Hmm?

427
00:22:43,495 --> 00:22:45,555
If this is too
much, we can stop.

428
00:22:45,965 --> 00:22:47,456
No, yeah, I'm good. I'm swaying.

429
00:22:47,566 --> 00:22:48,829
Sorry. All right.

430
00:22:48,934 --> 00:22:52,769
Okay, now guide
mom down to her pillow.

431
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:57,804
And, moms, this
is the best part.

432
00:22:58,177 --> 00:22:59,440
Foot massage.

433
00:23:00,813 --> 00:23:02,782
This is great if you
have a headache.

434
00:23:03,649 --> 00:23:06,517
And who remembers the
one place not to massage?

435
00:23:06,785 --> 00:23:07,809
Ankles.

436
00:23:09,488 --> 00:23:11,821
Everyone, this is Max,
the Medical Director.

437
00:23:12,324 --> 00:23:14,336
Yeah, I got a follow-up question.
Why are we giving foot massages

438
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:16,591
